-- General Electric Wins $300 Million Power, Water Plant Contracts in Oman
-- Ayesha Daya
-- 2010-07-06T08:23:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/general-electric-wins-300-million-power-water-plant-contracts-in-oman.html

          
          
             General Electric Co. received
contracts of about $300 million to provide five gas turbines and
signed a 15-year service agreement for a power plant in Salalah,
southwest Oman.  
 The Salalah independent water and power plant will have a
capacity of 445 megawatts of electricity and 15 million imperial
gallons a day of desalinated water, GE said in a statement
received by e-mail today.  
